for some of your good buffs instead.<br><br>A few days ago, a 60 sk gank that jumped me while I was xping was able to stun me using bash skill, every couple of tries. Bash*stun* Bash*stun* Bash *stun*...Guildie SK said bash was significantly improved this last patch.  Maybe when bash was given to clerics, it was improved generally as well? /shrug<br><br>This same sk, uber geared by his long stint in an anti-gank guild (before he went to the griefer side) finally almost went down vs my avge geared medium sized guilded monk (due to some timely heals from an alt) when he hit harmshield and was able to do the &quot;vox port out&quot;, racing to vox lair and getting banished with no life showing. He then shouted to the zone for half an hour like an ass about how &quot;with harmshield he is invincible&quot; and how he will &quot;never die&quot; again in pvp.<br><br><br>I don't know what Verant's thinking but making a super powered pvp class (sks) much stronger with the resist and dot stacking changes, with harmshield and with improved bashing, (go check out shadowknight.org, and see how many of them brag about how &quot;no class should ever be able to beat them&quot;) anyway these changes don't seem to be in the interest of balancing whatsoever. Ok, ok EQ is primarily &quot;not a pvp game&quot;, whatever, but doesn't it make sense they should not ignore pvp balance issues totally, not only for duels but for the thousands who do actually enjoy the zeks? <br><br>If pvp was better implemented in EQ I bet we'd see many more players playing on the zeks (look at the initial huge interest in SB, a game structured around pvp) but due to people &quot;giving up&quot; on VI's version of pvp (likely bc of a widespread perception VI has 'given up' on pvp balance), I think is the real reason the zeks are less populated than they could be. <br><br>But I digress.<br><br>What's this long, semi whiney post about? A couple things. <br><br>1) I'm hoping VI does some similar &quot;fixes&quot; to monks, to make us more effective in pvp.  We need a better way to interrupt.  Some reports I've heard of dragon punch knockback suggest it can work in pvp to interrupt, but looking at details of the skill on lucy's it suggests it has a 18 sec recharge? At any rate SK's in particular can bash and stun like crazy now from my experience, along with their large retinue of spells, skills, and VERY nice hps/ac/resist that is not so hard to attain,what with the nice values VI puts on alot of plate armor. We need some very reliable interrupt skills at least that work this way in pvp. Take away any delay in dragon punch knockback, if there is one (I'm still 10 aaxp away from finding out firsthand).<br><br>2) Keep retuning the pvp resist system, engulfing darkness/snare shouldn't be sticking on a 60 monk with 150+ MR the first try, that spell is just too devastating in pvp to be so easy to stick. It can be instant death to a melee all too often, given the unpredictability of pumice in removing top buffs. (For those who didn't know, golem wands and all other instant cast pumice effects that I know of have all been nerfed to be 3.0-4.0 or worse casting time).<br><br>3) Finally I'd like to hear some from other 60 monks about aaxp skills that have improved their dueling/pvp skills. How has dragon punch worked for you, at least vs the non pure casters (hybrids, with a lesser channeling skill, I'd think it would work better against than the pures)..ANy other skills in particular? I can easily see CA and CS helping in melee v melee jousting battles, any other things you've found to help alot?<br><br>steel<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ublytzz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blytzz</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://blytzz.freewebspace.com/images/train.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grand Master</span><br>  Post