http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31982.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> pvp </span><hr size=1> I expected alot of whiny stuff here about how &quot;EQ is not a pvp game&quot; despite my clear comments in my post directly confronting that issue so these posts don't bother or surprise me.  <br><br>If it weren't for pvp me and many many folks I know would have quit EQ long ago, it's the &quot;last frontier&quot; for many in EQ and the most exciting way to play for quite a few. But this isn't a post debating pvp in EQ, there's really no debate, either you like it or you don't, I quit trying to convince people of anything about it a couple years ago shortly after VZ and TZ were born (I now play exclusively on RZ).<br><br>Anyway my question about dragon punch knockback: We get the skill &quot;dragon punch&quot; really early in our monk life (Iksars get tail rake, same delay/dm etc.), and I know it refreshes quickly, in about 2.5 secs. That's not my question. My question concerns the aaxp &quot;proc&quot; called knockback, that works off of DP to push the target back about 3 ft.  I mentioned that Lucy's states it has a 18 sec recharge time. I'm wondering if this means that it takes about 18 secs for it to proc again as you are dragon punching away, or if in fact it can proc each time you hit dragon punch (giving it a 2.5 sec refresh time, for all practical purposes).  If anyone who has it wants to comment on it, and on how effective it is or isn't in pvp vs hybrids, and also vs. pure casters, thx in advance.<br><br>steel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uryumasters1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ryumasters1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 503<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/14/02 2:03:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31982.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pvp </span><hr size=1> I have been thinking of starting a side toon on a pvp just for fun.<br><br>What I really would like is if I could convince a friend of mine to join me. Think it would be pretty cool, and we could cover each others back if someone tried to jump us. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelbeaner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>El Beaner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/14/02 2:45:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31982.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pvp </span><hr size=1> before resist changes dragon punch was very rarely resisted.  not is isnt rare to see it resisted half the time.  even with a tranq there's nothing you can do against casters getting snared at 150 mr.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzadkiel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zadkiel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 9/29/02 6:08:46 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhaass.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haass</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/14/02 3:54:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31982.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pvp </span><hr size=1> Ya, and before the changes, most casters were totally useless against melee PvP.  Shamans had the disease line to use on you if they don't have malo.  Necros have ignite blood and splurt (pumiced), enchanters are just walking corpses...<br><br>Now the tables are turned, i'm sure some of your caster buddies you've been ganking repeatedly in dungeons are happy to finally be able to return the favor.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uyuffierz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yuffie RZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 353<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/14/02 5:03:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31982.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pvp </span><hr size=1> too be honest I haven't had any troubles with the resist system on both the mobs and players. My MR is 39. THREE NINE, and I still resist most spells as I normally do from most mobs and players.<br><br>I'm kinda glad I don't play on a carebear server... Oops.. Bluebie server I should say. You guy's have been too sodomized by the new resist system to be carebears now. <p>-Yuffie<BR><BR>[Fri Mar 29 14:47:36 2002] You kick sebilite juggernaut for 268 points of damage. <BR><BR>[Fri Apr 05 21:36:52 2002] You kick Xenevorash for 44 points of damage.<BR>[Fri Apr 05 21:36:52 2002] You have slain Xenevorash!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usteeldestiny.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Steeldestiny</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/14/02 12:51:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31982.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> pvp</span><hr size=1> Dragon punch knockback is now resisted alot? Here I am on my class board, monkly-business, and this thread I started to get support and ideas about monks in duels and in pvp situations has been almost ignored by my class, but hijacked by casters.<br><br>This from Haas:<br>__________________________________________<br>Ya, and before the changes, most casters were totally useless against melee PvP. Shamans had the disease line to use on you if they don't have malo. Necros have ignite blood and splurt (pumiced), enchanters are just walking corpses...<br><br>Now the tables are turned, i'm sure some of your caster buddies you've been ganking repeatedly in dungeons are happy to finally be able to return the favor. <br><br>______________________________________________<br><br>I found this hilarious.  <br>Go look at the rosters on RZ' gank guilds(the lower lvl ones all the way up to the ones with 60s in them) and you will find about 95-98% casters in every one of them.  This is not some fluke or strange anomaly. This is because for the style of pvp they do, grief ganking, the fast kill is king, and the ability to be highly effective in so-so no drop gear only(rallos is still one item loot) favors casters. <br>It's been this way from the start, and nothing VI has done has changed it. Why they have been implementing changes that are making the ganks more and more powerful, in light of the above easily verified imbalance already in favor of the caster griefer, raises alot of questions but makes no sense.<br>Beyond any doubt, casters have a large advantage outdoors in pvp, taking advantage of the ghosting bugs, shadowstep spells, and the other easy ways they have to gain distance between them and the melee.<br><br>All the resist and stacking changes VI just made are serving only to make casters king in indoor settings as well, as &quot;Haas&quot; above, tips his hat to.  As a 60 monk I've been having engulfing darkness stick on me through 157 MR first try. That spell is almost game over to a melee, and it's sticking through very good resists. What it's done if anything is make the sk the undisputed king of indoor pvp, with his darkness line sticking easily, his ability to fd helping him with the mobs that often get involved, his ability to easily stun without any resistance checks ramped up even in the latest patch, his lifetaps and harmtouch virtually unresistible and the disc that turn HT into a 1k+ in pvp insta dm spell and the aaxp that turns it into a 1k-ish lifetap, both virtually unresistible too.<br><br>Does this not bother any of you, fellow monks? I was hoping that DP knockback was going to help me regain some ability to fight sks, at least indoors where my strengths are, but it's sounding like its not that hard to resist with half decent resists. <br>Is it ok to you that regardless of how much labor you do in the game to improve your character, that VI keeps making other classes stronger in pvp settings (and the blues here , in duel settings) and has done nothing for us in that setting? Is everyone so happy with fighting computer controlled and predictable mobs, that monks have grown lackadaisical in regards to how we are holding up in one on ones vs other classes? <br><br>If so that's sad. Alot of people here posted that &quot;EQ is not a pvp game&quot;. Go visit the Zeks and you will quickly see that that is false, you can indeed play eq vs other players. I suspect what they really mean is &quot;EQ implementation of pvp is not good enough to warrant playing it with pvp as a significant part of the play&quot;. Well, this deserves a few words.<br><br>I played Age of Empires, a rt strategy game, vs others, and enjoyed it.<br><br>I plyed Warcraft 2, a rt strategy game, vs others, and enjoyed it.<br><br>I played Starcraft, a rt strategy game, against others, and enjoyed it.<br><br>I played Red Alert, a rt strategy game, against others, and enjoyed it.<br><br>I played about myth, and giants:citizen kabuto, and about a dozen other games, vs others, and enjoyed it.<br><br>Similarly, I play EQ, a rts mmorpg, vs others, and I enjoy it.<br><br>Every game I listed above had its issues with pvp. AoE and RA quickly evolved into tank rush type domination due to imbalance favoring certain types of craft/fighters.<br><br>Warcraft had many bugs that enabled the kewl doods to use all sorts of tricks to avoid losses and climb the &quot;ladder&quot; through trickery. <br><br>Giants was unbalanced in its classes favoring the siren type people over the mechs.<br><br>Every single game I've ever played against others has had its issues but every one I've taken up was fun and EQ has been no exception.  It's not perfect, but it's still very fun and is worth the time in my and many others opinion to post things like this thread to try to help fix it rather than dismiss it as a waste.<br><br>So the question remains, what can VI do to improve the monk class and strengthen us a little in light of the recent caster/bash/stacking changes. Any ideas? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwoodansz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WoodanSZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/14/02 4:05:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31982.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pvp</span><hr size=1> I never fight SKs anymore.<br>200+ lifetap, 1600 dmg insta unresistable DD, snare, hit hard, stun like mad, tons of hp, buffs, DA spell.  They are not worth it.<br>I would rather fight a manaburn Wizard.<br><br>I am from SZ and have never avoided pvp, but now that im nearing 60 pvp is a joke.  Sick class imbalances, and the fact that you LOSE EXP when you die here, really makes me not wan't to play anymore.   They should remove all penalties from these joke servers because I am sick of paying them because some asshole with manaburn or HT thinks they are a pvp god hitting a button for DT. <p><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/snorcrax/fullsize/signature.jpg"><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzhyangwoo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zhyang Woo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/17/02 7:08:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31982.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pvp</span><hr size=1> For the record, I play a monk on Sullon Zek, base MR of 141 when PvPing.  Before the patch, I'd never been killed by a green con (which is anyone lower than five levels below me).  After the patch, snare or root lands *immediately* upon first casting and lasts the full duration.  Since the patch, I've run into two groups of green cons--waaay low green cons, as in 20-30th level, three people in each group.  They killed me both times (a snared monk is about as effective as an orc pawn, for those of you who don't play on the PvP servers).<br><br>I'm taking a break until the next patch, when they're supposed to address it.  This is the latest word from former Sullon Zek GM Rytan, who is now a dev:<br><br>&quot;Yeah we changed the resist system for PvP from what it is now on the PvP servers.  It's based on a diminishing returns system so you can't ever get totally immune to certain types of spells, but it's a little easier to get to the &quot;protected&quot; level where you won't get hit every time.  Should be updated next patch.&quot;<br><br>I wrote back and asked:<br><br>&quot;So what's a rough estimate on the protected level?  150 MR?  175?&quot;<br><br>He responded:<br><br>&quot;It's higher then it used to be, but I don't have the actual formula.  I'm guessing your 150 should be adequate in most cases if you're not fighting someone who's red.  I'm glad for the changes actually.  It used to be that anything over about 140 in a resiste made you all but immune to spells of that type other then damage spells.&quot;<br><br>So while I'm pretty much going offline until the next patch, I'll have to check out the rebalancing when the next patch hits.  I completely agree with alot of the people out there--the resistance nerf makes playing a monk on a PvP utterly impossible, unless you're just doing the usual raid/xp session (and not getting interrupted by the other two teams).<br><br>I saw a bard with 300 MR get rooted by a level 14 wizard.  And although PvP servers are the red-headed step-children of EverQuest, I would imagine that Verant makes over $500,000 a year from us (gross, at least), so I kind of wish that whoever was in charge of this patch would've been paying attention a little more.  You'd think that when they do a resistance patch, they'd be thinking about PvP as well as the blue game.  Obviously, they didn't.<br><br>There'll probably be quite a bit of fine-tuning over the next six months with this, so be sure to /feedback it.  Believe it or not, they do read them.<br><br>Z.<br> <p>Zhyang Woo<br>Avatar of Lizard Sexiness, RETIRED<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=117842">My Ridiculously Crappy Stuff</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukazdun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kazdun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 219<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/18/02 1:34:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonkly